This was such a great stop! We were visiting from out if town and this was recommended to us by a local. It is very casual and we were seated promptly. < Text>
This is one of the best family restaurants in town. They have an amazing salsa and a very reasonably priced menu with great specials. Show up for happy hour and get 25% off cocktails and other sweet deals like cheap quesadillas. If they ever have lengua as a special, get it it's amazing. The chile verde and Chile Colorado are awesome. Great tamales and enchiladas.</Text>

< Review>
Mellow vibes in this quiet restaurant by the beach. The waitress always has a smile on her face, welcoming all who walk in. Unassuming, straight forward, and consistency are it's strengths. Chipotle Benedict, chorizo and eggs, and the fish sandwich are my favs. Drop in for a quick and affordable meal.<//Review>

<username>John<//username><time>1476553771439< /time>< rate>
4< /rate>
< review>
We ended up here by accident as we actually came to the area to go to Outerlands (also reviewed). Outerlands had along line up so we came across the street to the Sea Breeze. On first appearance we weren't sure whether we wanted to eat here as the atmosphere and decor of the interior was was a bit below our liking. However, it was getting later in the afternoon and we did not want to go elsewhere. We were very glad we made the decision to stay as the food was terrific and the service was fast, attentive and friendly. The Outerlands is a bit more upscale in appearance and the food is a bit more inventive but we would definitely stop at Sea Breeze again.</review>

< Review>
The storage units themselves are decent and clean, but definitely a bit overpriced depending on time of year (I took it regardless cause this was the closest storage unit to my house). The customer service on the other hand, absolutely horrendous, by the older lady at the reception. On the multiple occasions I went to the location, I met 4 separate individuals working there, 3 of which were extremely nice and courteous, but this older lady was absolutely horrendous and rude, was always on the phone and was completely unhelpful, regularly passing snarky comments, rolling her eyes, shouting and sometimes straight up ignoring my questions. I wish I could remember her name, sadly I can't and I have no desire to go back to this pace to find out. Might do business with Public Storage again, but definitely never with this location.</Review>

<rate>2</rate><Review>i have rented a 10x30 unit at this location for over five years.  The storage facility is adequate and the staff is generally helpful.  However, new customers should be aware of their practice of penalizing long-term renters with ridiculously large rate hikes, far in excess of inflation or the market rates for new contracts.  The rent on my unit was initially $392/mo in February 2014.  It is now $811/mo.  Meanwhile, new customers are paying around $500 for similar units.  I cannot recommend this business to anyone who foresees a long-term storage need.  These are the kinds of rate increases you can expect if you rent a storage space here:

7/14: $461
7/15: $512
7/16: $579
7/17: $643
7/18: $727
7/19: $811<//Review>< Pics>

< Review>
Terrible overall experience. First of all the initial payment for the first month came out to 50% more than the stated monthly price due to hidden fees such as processing fees and mandatory insurance. I then came in the next day asking if I could get a refund because I no longer needed the storage unit. They told me that they could not give me one which was fine. Several days later they called and said they were in the process of refunding me. However, at this point I did not want the refund because the truck I was going to use to move was no longer available to me. Then 8 days after I started the lease they told me I was behind on a payment. I called them to see what they meant by that and they said I needed to pay $3.60, which must have been an error on their end. Normally a fee of this much would not be a big deal but I was not able to make the payment online because the online account did not recognize my email address despite the fact that they had been communicating with me with the exact email I entered. I called the helpline on their website to get assistance but there was nothing they could do so the only way I could make a payment was to go down to the storage yard in person which was far from where I was living and extremely inconvenient. My overall experience was very negative and I will never use public storage again.< /Review>

< review>
This review is in two parts. First for the corporate side and second for the staff who works on site.

Part One: Corporate
Zero Stars

The first thing you should know about Public Storage is BE PREPARED FOR LARGE FEE INCREASES!

They don't even have the decency to wait a year. Four months after they lure you in with a Bait & Switch con they will raise your fees. A lot.

I spend tens of thousands of dollars a year at this facility and corporate cares ZERO for customer loyalty. Know that you will be treated like a dupe once they get you signed up.

Also, once you are a loyal customer they won't let you leave mid month. So if you stay one hour past the last day of the month they charge you for the entire month. They used to pro-rate but no longer. Just another way to be scummy and money grab. Pretty sad way to do business.

Part 2
Excellent staff! Five Stars!

Many thanks to Kevin, Tamika, Brittnee and the team who have all gone above and beyond to be extra helpful to me. Their commitment to customer service is THE BEST. Many thanks.

**This part of the review is only for the staff, the policies of the corporation are far less satisfactory. If not for the friendly and engaged people working here I would have taken my storage business elsewhere long ago.<//review>

< review>
I have never used storage before and really didn't think there was much to it. When I got to the facility it was clean and the employees were helpful. The manager who helped me was Art and was very helpful and patient, he showed me a couple different sizes after he asked me just what I was storing and explaining how to put it in there like a puzzle to utilize the space to get in the smallest space possible. He did offer to get me loaded up on boxes but they seemed a bit much. I will say they do like to stay in touch with their customers as I got a bunch of calls until I answered to first come in and rent the space and a couple reminder calls that the rent is due. I guess it's not that bothersome since the phone calls are friendly and just trying to do their job. As much of a great experience it has been, it's still an extra bill I could do without :-)</review>

< text>
They have something for everyone. Circuit training, brand new machines, massage, all for $19.99 a month. Also personal training in group setting and all access for $55 total a month flat fee. Ask for Jose . Watch out for bait n switch tactics. Although their $19.99 a month membership says it includes group classes, you'll come to discover after you've paid in full that there are no group classes cause they cancelled them, yet they took your money already and then they try to upsell you on Evo Fit classes that has its own membership and you have to pay for it separately. The gym definitely has a mismanagement issue which creates miscommunication and confusion for the customers.< /text>

I would NOT recommend establishing a gym membership at the Fit Republic, in Atascadero. They need to better train their manager's at handling customer's escalated issues, also returning phone calls, especially when they promise to do so, as well as establishing proper training that includes reciting their rules over the telephone, to those looking to renew their memberships. I have concluded Fit Republic is neither upfront nor honest about their "rules," that pertain to membership cancellations/refunds.

Originally, I had signed up for a year long membership, prior to changing the name, and hiring new management at the facility. Overall (aside from their music selection) I was pleased and personally had no issues, although plenty of people I know personally and professionally, had several bad experiences mostly pertaining to having their checking accounts debited repeatedly for months after they left the gym.

Once my membership had expired, the gym employee that I spoke to via telephone, insisted that I pay for their one year membership upfront, for the best rate possible. He failed to inform me of a single disclaimer, like I would be forfeiting all of my money if I cancelled my membership.

Unexpectedly I recently moved to the coast. So, while running errands one day, I entered into the gym to speak to management about receiving a refund for the remaining months I could no longer use for I was no longer able to attend their gym. The new female manager informed me there were no refunds. I explained that I was never told this important information over the telephone. The staff should have recited this prior to the renewal process. I was quite upset to find out only after the fact that they were already paid in full. I was then told she would call me back in a few weeks after she spoke to the gym owner directly, for guidance.

It is now February. I have yet to receive any sort of refund or a single phone call as promised.

I decided to call the gym, 5 days ago but there was no answer. I left a message including my name, phone number, and requested a phone call back. I have yet to hear back from the manager that I spoke to originally months ago or from a staff member.

All and all, it feels like I have fallen victim to a scam. This incident shows true unprofessionalism, through and through.

I expect a refund for the several months I had remaining or some sort of solution from the owner. They could allow me to transfer the rest of my membership time of 7 months to a family member or friend living in town. Rather I am just being ignored.<//Text>

I was explained that since they require a 30 day notice, I will be still charged for the month of June. I checked my credit card statement and discovered that I'm still being charged for the membership in August! I called the gym three times before I was able to speak with a manager. I'm being told that they are showing me cancelling the membership in the month of July, which is completely impossible since I haven't left So Cal since June,1. I was told that their corporate office is working on resolving the issue and getting the refund but I haven't heard anything at all. This place is a scam, and if you happen to do any business with them, have them PRINT EVERY SINGLE FORM FOR YOU! Don't believe in their excuses, they will find a thousand more excuses not to refund you. If they say that they can't print a form, take a picture on your phone. Learn on my mistake and on mistakes of many others as you can see from the reviews.

Update: I happened to visit SLO past weekend and decided to stop by at EvoFit on 9/16 and see their manager. Once I asked for a manager, the guy named Johny stated that he is a new manager but he's not on a clock and just walked out. He wouldn't even listen to what the issue was, just went to work out. The front desk lady took my information and promised that Johny would call me back Monday. I haven't heard back from anybody. It figures! Johny, Johny, there is no such a thing as a manager on a clock. If you run a place, you run it even you happened to simply work out there. This is not how tou start your management career! < Review>
Great burgers with a lovely view. The onion rings were delicious as well. Burger had great charring on the edges, onion rings were crisp and flavorful. There is a sign in the window that says "This is not fast food...", which is true, however, it is worth the wait and you honestly won't mind waiting if you can grab a seat at the long counter overlooking the river and just watch the water go by. Great place to grab a bite after doing some tasting at the Old Sugar Mill!< /Review>

<user_id>109523456914494629646</user_id>< name>
James Dunn</name>
<Time>1535585523960</Time><Rating>4</Rating>< review>
Accessible by boat, but land North of diner about 1000 feet.  You will see a large number of rocks.  There is no "nice" dockage available to the public.  Do not land at the marina, it is private property.

Veggieburger.  Quaint, picturesque, and sure to inspire sharing a related story.

Take a plastic bag with you and pick up a little trash where you beach to help retain landing privileges.

I am surprised the local cafe's, art studios, and shopping businesses haven't built a public pay by the hour dock to bring in business.

Retirees travel in groups, and have the largest disposable income of any demographic.  They love their boats.</review>

<text>I can absolutely recommend Right Solution without reservation.

I just bought a 2011 Saab 9-3 convertible, and wanted to get the oil changed, have it checked out, etc.  I tried Ed Little and Cal, but neither one works on Saabs.  However, Ed Little's recommended Right Solution.  Which is noteworthy in and of itself.

ANYway, I brought it in right when they opened (at 8am on a Wed).  Walter jumped in the car with me, and took it for a test drive.  Really appreciate that he did that.  So we got back, and he had his guys go over the car for an hour with a proverbial fine tooth comb.  When they were done, they brought me into the garage and gave me a bit of a technical tour of the car, which was great!  Then Walter told me it was perfect...not a single thing wrong.  Asked me to bring it back in 5k miles for an oil change and in 6k to have the break pads checked.  I totally expected to have the oil changed because the selling dealer said it might need it.

When I asked Walter what I owed him for the time, he said 'nothing.'   As in nada.  Zip.  Zero.  Zilch.  I even insisted on paying for the hour of his tech's time.  He was adamant that I pay nothing.  Said that the check up was free.  He just asked me to tell my friends about his shop.  Which I will!

He could have changed my oil, replaced the break pads, and charged me $100 for the hour of time.  I would have paid $400 without even thinking about it.  Instead, Walter took the high road.  I'm beyond impressed.

You know what else I noticed?  He really respects his technicians.  Treats them like friends.  Maybe that seems random and irrelevant, but I think it speaks to his integrity.

I actually found an honest mechanic.  So, so relieved.< /text><resp>None<//resp>< time>

<time>1360631827958<//time><Rating>3</Rating><Text>Don't let them near your RV.

Sorry I called them.  I scheduled to leave on a dry camping trip and I wasn't sure about my house batteries so I searched the Web for batteries.  I found Right Solutions Inc. who was more than willing to come to my home and install 4 new batteries.  The first mistake I made other than using their services, was assuming the installer new what he was doing and could connect everything the way it was.  When he finished I checked the charge on my monitor and found that the batteries weren't fully charged.  I was informed that these were new batteries and just needed to charge overnight, so I connected my battery charger and charged the batteries over night.  They were charged the next morning and as I left for my vacation I was confident that I wouldn't have a battery problem but I was wrong.  The next morning my batteries were completely dead and I had to use my generator which should have recharged my batteries through the inverter, but they didn't charge.  I called the warranty number on the battries and they sent me to the nearest dealer who checked the batteries and said they were good but could have been installed wrong. This was out of their expertise.  To make a long story short, since I left my battery charger at home I ended up purchacing a new on at WalMart in Arizona to charge my batteries. I finnaly had a mechanic look at my batteries and it was determined that the insaller connected a wire from the inverter to the negative side instead of the positive.  He corrected it and the system started charging. When I returned home I contacted Right Solutions requesting some type of compensation for the money I spent and was told that their installer experienced and would not have done anything wrong however, we all make mistakes.  They refused to compensate me for the extra money I spent instead they want to have their electrician look at my RV and see if there is a problem.  Of course there's no problem now I paid to have it fixed.  I will continue to try to resolve this issue but it doesn't look hopeful.  I thought I was saving money but it ended up costing me more.  Next time I will buy from Interstate.

I received a call from Rudy the owner of Right Solutions who informed me that he didn't know about the problem I had with the batter installation. It seems that the supervisor talked to me. <gmapID>0x809aa019b74beefb:0x6ff273730b722e22<//gmapID></record></dataset><record>
< review>
I love this store. I go there for Magic the Gathering products. Mike always has a good selection of accessories for tcg's. And while I don't play table top games, it seems like he's got a good selection of things like miniatures, paints and accessories for table top gaming as well..

What impresses me most is that the prices of his sealed Magic products are so competitive. You can get a booster box, packs and other sealed products for pretty cheap.

The only downside I would say is Mike doesn't deal in singles. If you are looking to buy single MTG, YGO, or Pok√©mon cards you'll have to go somewhere else. As for everything else, Mike either has it, or he can get it.

When we can get back to playing in stores. His store is fun to play at as well; great crowd, clean bathroom, the new store arrangement is excellent to. If you are into physical gaming like trading cards, table top or board games, Launchpad is a great place to shop at!</review>

<Gmap_id>0x809aa019b74beefb:0x6ff273730b722e22< /Gmap_id><Name>Tommy P<//Name>< review>
When they first moved to Lodi after they flopped in Stockton they rented the location of the former adult video store as their new store.

Why? Because it was right next to Lodi Grapevine. They needed to steal customers. They tried the same thing with Al's comics in Stockton but failed.

Their Lodi location is small and cramped. Somewhat decent selection of comics but limited gaming supplies. Staff is polite enough until you ask them about other shops in the area (Stockton, Manteca, and even Sacramento).

That's when they go into their sales pitch about how they're the best and the other shops are run by "retards".<//review>

<user_id>100306317624822760422< /user_id><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< review>
If you like huge plates of mediocre seafood (at best) this is the place for you. Our server was very competent but I only go because my elderly sister likes the huge plates of stuff. Certainly not for the food. The pasta was overcooked. The two types of lobster were overcooked. The shrimp were tasteless. The biscuits could have used a few extra minutes in the oven but the flavor was what I expected. The mashed potatoes had been around a while. The hostess was chatting away with some other workers and couldn't have missed me waiting at her stand for a long awaited table. Spend your hard-earned somewhere else if you want seafood. There are so many better places.</review>

117423688963131804290<//UserId.>
< user_name>
John D<//user_name>
< date>
1583294180860< /date>
<Rating>4</Rating>< Review>
I like red lobster but you have to understand why your coming here. All the food we have had here is cooked very well.  Service can be hit or miss. Our challenge has always been around crab legs.

My wife loves crab legs. They are cooked well and taste good but one thing or another always happens. We either don't get the right tools to crack them open, they forget to cut them for easier access to the meat, or they are cold.

I have always gotten, lobster in some form or another had it has been great. Fish is cooked well and taste great.

Their biscuits always has to much salt. Some people like it, we don't.

You pay less at red lobster but you need to order to their strong suits and keep expectations in check.

They are in a different class than Kings Fish, and Taps is in an even different class. I know your spending $35 for a meal, but at taps that meal would be $70 and up, but it would be worth every bit it.

If I just want some lobster, then I go to Red Lobster.  If I want a someone to cater to my every need, be in a much more formal setting, top of the line quality, then I got to Taps, but I also pay for it.

My wife will now knows not to order crab legs.

We will be back.</Review>

None< /Pics>

<Date>1546707557380<//Date><Rating>2<//Rating><Review>The hubs and I went to celebrate our wedding anniversary, and I think we simply chose the wrong time of day to show up. It was just before 4:30pm, and, at least, five staff members showed up behind us. There was no one out front, so we waited, and waited, as crew member after crew member walked this way and that. One person eventually said someone would be with us, and more time passed. Our waitress was very nice. She seemed quite distracted, however. Our section wasn't very packed, but I suppose it was busy enough. We waited quite some time for our waters, and the biscuits. After taking our order, the food arrived rather quickly. My mashed potatoes were cold. It was odd, because the rest of my food was hot. Perhaps they were placed on the plate first, before the rest of the food was cooked? We needed tartar sauce, ketchup, and cocktail sauce. When it finally arrived, there wasn't enough for each plate. We were asked if we wanted more biscuits. We did, but they never came. Perhaps she didn't here our, "Yes" response? Also, there was an upcharge on one of the drinks, when we specifically asked if there was a deviation from the listed price. The hot food was delicious. The cold mashed potatoes was very disappointing. The lack of attention to the specific requested condiments and additional biscuits, was very disappointing, as well. We did receive a refill on our water, and after specifying again, we received the correct number of condiments and lids for our leftovers. By the time we left, it was busy. Every table in our section was filled, and there was a line out front. I have mixed feelings about this visit, as it seems things got better by the end, when it was actually busy. We've received better service from Denny's, on a Saturday morning, and they stay packed!  Red Lobster earned two stars. I hope they can redeem themselves, IF I ever decide to go back. #disappointed</Review>< Pics>

< review>
Arrived at noon for lunch.  We were a party of 4.  The place was not busy  but we were seated in the bar area and were the only ones in this area.  This is not my ideal place to sit.  Our server was the bar tender.  Service was lacking big time.  We ordered the fish and chips.  It was grease soaked and the fish was very mushy.  The fettuccini with alfredo sauce and crab had over cooked gummy pasta very little pasty sauce.
The only highlight was the salad and garlic biscuits  were good.  Will not be going back.
Quality of food has really gone down hill.  This used to be my favorite place.</review>

< text>
First restaurant my father and I went to after his lengthy hospitalization (it's like 300 feet from Kaiser Permanente). The food was okay, however the service was a little slow that night. There were not many children, which is a bonus for those whom would like to minimize the probability of louder ambient conversations; personally, it doesn't bother me. If you're looking for some seafood, or surf and turf while attending/visiting Kaiser Permanente, Red Lobster provides a nice alternative to Kaiser's basement (and vending machines).< /text>
